 Godfrey Frederick Allan Kennell (94), better known as Geoff passed away peacefully on Sunday. Geoff was actively involved in the Nelspruit Methodist congregation, Nelspruit Hospice, Lowveld Toast Masters society, Catholic Church Carpet Bowls, and will be fondly remembered for his interesting short stories and quirky rhymes and poems. Geoff was a regular contributor to lowvelder.co.za, and published many of his short stories in his blog section, titled Off the Cuff with Goeff Kennell. In celebration of his life and work, here are some of the pieces he shared with our readers:    Read more here 